Add Ports on FW:
  firewall-cmd --stat (check its running)
  firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-port=80/tcp (adds port 80/http permanently)
  firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-port=443/tcp (adds port 443/https permanently)
  firewall-cmd --reload (reloads service)
Check ports:
   firewall-cmd --list-ports 
   
Install HTTPD:
  (sudo) yum install httpd 
Enable/Start:
  systemctl enable httpd.service
  systemctl start httpd.service

Test connection to webpage 
remove welcome and customize for self use

Install PHP:
  (sudo) yum install php

Create PHP script to run on webserver
test script and avigate to wenserver direcotry 
